<TITLE> Editors concerned over Nurul Kabir's death threat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 2 (bdnews24.com)  Editors of national daily newspapers have expressed deep concern over repeated death threats given to New Age editor Nurul Kabir. In a joint statement on Tuesday, the editors alleged that no effective measures were taken although the police had been informed of the matter. "This is a threat to freedom of expressions of a citizen, as well as a newspaper." The statement said that such threats also impeded the democratic process. The English daily newspaper, that Kabir heads is published from Dhaka and known for its strong criticism of the ruling government and its generally anti-establishment stance. The signatories of the statement include Mahbubul Alam of the Independent, Rahat Khan of the Ittefaque, Matiur Rahman of the daily Prothom Alo, Golam Sarwar of Samakal, Mahfuz Anam of the Daily Star and Abed Khan of Kaler Kant
